need to make sure the in-memory DB logger is open. I don't think RAFileHybrid requires a database file. For the testing part, I need to try \\\"hybridRandomAccessFileClosesMappedNioStore\\\" with a temporary file, writing bytes, checking the length, and closing it. I wonder if I should assert that the file length is at least 16MB?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing Gradle setup**\\n\\nI need to focus on using a native image, and I wonder if hsqldb requires awt. It seems I already have a native build. I’m thinking about whether the top-level class needs to be public and if the test method can be package-private. I need to add the Test import in build.gradle, but I’m unsure if the Test class is already imported. I’ll check if tasks.withType(Test) is in use, then I can start writing.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_VBq7x003mVHFDL1h72LoiRpX|fc_0bd66787a39fb3ac016a1182c1da9881a2969321e4c8256fb1", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/src/test/java/org_hsqldb/hsqldb/RAFileNIOTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_hsqldb.hsqldb;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.sql.Connection;\nimport java.util.Arrays;\n\nimport org.hsqldb.Database;\nimport org.hsqldb.Session;\nimport org.hsqldb.jdbc.JDBCConnection;\nimport org.hsqldb.jdbc.JDBCDataSource;\nimport org.hsqldb.persist.RAFileHybrid;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\n\npublic class RAFileNIOTest {\n    private static final long NIO_THRESHOLD = 8L * 1024L * 1024L;\n\n    @TempDir\n    Path temporaryDirectory;\n\n    @Test\n    void closeUnmapsMappedBufferUsedByHybridRandomAccessFile() throws Exception {\n        String databaseName = \"rafilenio_\" + Long.toUnsignedString(System.nanoTime());\n        String randomAccessFileName = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"cached-table.data\").toString();\n\n        try (Connection connection = openConnection(databaseName)) {\n            Database database = databaseSession(connection).getDatabase();\n            byte[] expected = new byte[] { 3, 1, 4, 1, 5, 9 };\n\n            RAFileHybrid file = new RAFileHybrid(database, randomAccessFileName, false);\n\n            try {\n                assertThat(file.ensureLength(NIO_THRESHOLD + expected.length)).isTrue();\n                file.seek(NIO_THRESHOLD);\n                file.write(expected, 0, expected.length);\n                file.seek(NIO_THRESHOLD);\n\n                byte[] actual = new byte[expected.length];\n\n                file.read(actual, 0, actual.length);\n\n                assertThat(actual).isEqualTo(expected);\n                assertThat(file.length()).isGreaterThanOrEqualTo(NIO_THRESHOLD + expected.length);\n            } finally {\n                file.close();\n            }\n\n            assertThat(temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"cached-table.data\")).exists();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static Connection openConnection(String databaseName) throws Exception {\n        JDBCDataSource dataSource = new JDBCDataSource();\n\n        dataSource.setUrl(\"jdbc:hsqldb:mem:\" + databaseName + \";shutdown=true\");\n        dataSource.setUser(\"SA\");\n        dataSource.setPassword(\"\");\n\n        return dataSource.getConnection();\n    }\n\n    private static Session databaseSession(Connection connection) throws Exception {\n        JDBCConnection hsqldbConnection = connection.unwrap(JDBCConnection.class);\n\n        return (Session) hsqldbConnection.getSession();\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 590, "output": 1563, "cacheRead": 35840, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37993, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, 